title: See All the Best Photos of Prince Harry's Trip to Angola
text: Today, Prince Harry continues his solo portion of the tour of Southern Africa. After visiting Bostwana yesterday, the Duke is in Angola this morning, following in the footsteps of his late mother Princess Diana in the fight to eradicate landmines. While in the country, Harry will not only travel to a de-mining field outside Dirico with the landmine clearance charity HALO Trust, but he will also unveil a plaque to mark the Queen’s Commonwealth Canopy project, and will visit the Huambo Orthopaedic Centre, which was also visited by Princess Diana in 1997. Here, the best photos of his trip to the country.
